# Catch-all: force-redirect ALL other root .html pages to /en/ versions.
# Uses :slug placeholder to match a single path segment (root-level only).
# The `!` (force) flag overrides Netlify's "file exists, serve file" default —
# without it, the existing root .html files would win and the redirect never fires.
# This was the root cause of GSC "Duplicate, Google chose different canonical" for
# 334 EN pages: Google saw root + /en/ as duplicates and sometimes picked root
# despite our canonical tags pointing to /en/.
/:slug.html             /en/:slug.html                     301!
